version: 0.6
- Platform & Architecture
  - Introduced module-oriented boundaries: moved legacy core domain logic into dedicated modules (`memory`, `moral_matrix`, `vision`, `system`) and kept `core` focused on orchestration/startup.
  - Added `SystemModule` facade (`backend/modules/system/service.py`) for config/runtime access and cross-module safe calls.
  - Added interaction policy layer (`backend/services/interaction_policy.py`) to enforce role-based capabilities for history/memory/edit/reroll actions.
- Auth, Session & Bootstrap
  - Added full auth flow (register/login/refresh/logout, guards/interceptor on frontend, auth routes/services on backend).
  - First registration now provisions `owner`; subsequent registrations default to `user`.
  - Startup pipeline stabilized: backend readiness-first launch flow (`run.py`), safer startup checks, schema bootstrap ordering, and DB-first config compatibility.
- DB-first Config & Character Management
  - Migrated to DB-first config access with split settings tables (`user_configs`, `user_tts_settings`, `user_vision_settings`) and runtime-safe wrappers.
  - Added character catalog endpoints and YAML import flow in system config routes.
  - Introduced active character model in `user_settings.active_character_id` and switched runtime routing/history loading to active-character resolution.
  - Added fallback/backfill logic: if active character is missing, resolve from latest history and persist to `user_settings`.
- Chat & Realtime Reliability
  - WebSocket pipeline hardened: run IDs, stop semantics, runtime trace streaming, better send safety, and richer error signaling.
  - Fixed reconnect/empty-state behavior in frontend chat and improved WS client robustness against transient disconnects.
  - Added per-run metadata persistence into history runtime fields (provider/model/usage/traces/timing).
- Memory & Moral Matrix
  - Added memory emulator route/workflow for staged retrieval inspection and debugging.
  - Expanded memory knowledge layer (`anchors`, `associations`) and owner-scoped access controls.
  - Moral Matrix route/provider path stabilized with safer character resolution and degraded-response fallback in failure scenarios.
- Voice/TTS/RVC
  - Voice settings UI was expanded with provider-aware controls and integrated RVC/XTTS related backend hooks.
  - Added RVC runtime assets/pipeline files and bootstrap services for model status/download/import flows.
  - Refactored TTS manager/service contracts to centralize provider selection, preview generation, and safer playback lifecycle.
- Synthesis (Image Generation)
  - Added synthesis module and routes with pluggable providers.
  - Introduced `Z-Image-Turbo` provider and a generic Diffusers provider path for local model-driven generation.
- Frontend Platform Upgrade
  - Added new feature modules/pages (`auth`, `memory`, `matrix`, `synthesis`, `audit`, `diary`) and expanded routing guards.
  - Introduced shared UI-kit components (`ui-button`, `ui-input`, `ui-select`, `ui-range`, `ui-checkbox`, `ui-textarea`, etc.) and unified icon registry/assets.
  - Updated config mappers/services for new backend schema and module settings.
- Storage & Paths
  - Consolidated model storage layout under `backend/storage/models/*` domains (vision, rvc, etc.) and aligned path constants.
  - Added/updated helper services for XTTS/RVC resources and model path resolution.
- Dependency & Runtime Notes
  - Updated `backend/requirements.txt` and frontend package set to support new auth/synthesis/TTS/UI capabilities.
  - Added/kept warnings/telemetry handling improvements (including optional runtime hardening for noisy libs on clean builds).

version: 0.5
- Localization & Logging
  - Added a `.env`-driven localization service with EN/RU dictionaries, automatic fallbacks, and cached lookups for backend modules.
  - Extended the logger to resolve localized strings, persist message keys/args, capture active language, and mirror localized output to the console.
  - Updated analyzer, memory, audio, voice, TTS, vision, and initialization flows to emit localized audit events with contextual parameters.
- Voice, TTS & Vision
  - Localized the entire VAD listener pipeline (startup, trigger handling, duplicate suppression) and audio playback threads with structured console prints.
  - ElevenLabs and offline TTS providers now report localized progress/errors, chunk counts, and synthesis timings; audio playback interruptions are localized per device.
  - Vision service, worker, and AppleVision provider log localized monitor/window selection, YOLO/SSIM metrics, capture errors, and inference lifecycle events.
- Memory & API
  - Memory routes and short-term memory helpers now output localized schema checks, refresh steps, and retrieval logs.
  - Analyzer provider manager and other backend utilities adopt the localization service for consistent RU/EN messaging across the stack.
- Backend & Core Systems
  - Introduced a `.env`-driven localization service with EN/RU dictionaries, cached loading, and fallback logic; wired it into the logger so every audit entry prints translated text with contextual parameters.
  - Added the Moral Matrix module (repository, heuristics, Ollama/OpenRouter providers with fallback manager) and hooked its evaluation results into the decision layer.
  - Rebuilt the high-level generation pipeline (`modules/generative/conversation.py`) to orchestrate streaming providers, sanitise attachments, split reasoning `<think>` blocks, and persist richer metadata in storage/history.
  - Expanded default configuration, DTOs, and routes with moral/analyzer/generation fields, plus helpers for PATCH updates and system prompt management.
- Voice & Audio Pipeline
  - Overhauled the TTS manager with provider retry/back-off, queue/worker controls, self-trigger protection, and detailed logging across Edge, ElevenLabs, gTTS, and offline fallbacks.
  - Localised the VAD listener (startup, trigger handling, duplicate suppression) and audio playback threads; console prints now mirror audit events with translated strings.
  - ElevenLabs and offline providers report download progress, synthesis timings, and error states via the localization layer; audio playback interruptions include per-device context.
- Vision & Memory
  - Vision service/worker emit localized diagnostics for monitor/window selection, YOLO counts, SSIM/optical-flow metrics, and capture failures; AppleVision provider logs localized load/ready/inference lifecycle messages.
  - Short-term memory schema checks, refresh routines, and analyzer provider fallbacks now surface localized console/audit output.
- Frontend & Tooling
  - Updated Angular config service/mappers to handle partial updates for new sections (moral, analyzer, system prompt) and aligned UI logging with backend schema changes.
  - Added RU/EN translation assets and localization helpers so the frontend mirrors backend language selection during diagnostics.
- Bugfix & Stability Improvements
  - Voice & TTS
    - Edge-TTS provider now checks service availability before fetching voices; if the service is unreachable, voices are skipped and not loaded into the frontend (8-second timeout threshold).
    - Added configuration flag for selecting offline TTS mode directly from the Audio settings.
  - Configuration & Visual Module
    - Fixed monitor selection and value assignment issues affecting the Vision module.
    - Restored proper handling of character name and owner name fields in configuration.
    - Fixed analyzer settings not applying correctly after updates.
    - Resolved an issue where Audio settings overwrote unrelated config sections on save.
    - Improved visual provider initialization and parameter mapping for stability.

version: 0.4
- Backend & LLM orchestration
  - Introduced modular analyzer and generative packages with provider managers that fail over between OpenRouter and Ollama, plus shared Ollama client helpers for text and vision chats.
  - Rewired generation streaming and synchronous paths through the new providers, centralizing error handling and audit logging around the fallback chain.
- Memory & Storage
  - Added a MemoryModule that can collect recent/session context via embeddings, integrate lorebook lookups, and report retrieval metadata.
  - Implemented a storage service + /api/media route to persist message attachments on disk, auto-upgrade the storage schema, and expose safe downloads.
- Config & API surface
  - Expanded config models, DTOs, and routes to cover analyzer, generator, memory, and media settings; refreshed mappers on both backend and frontend to keep camelCase ↔ snake_case conversions in sync.
  - Updated vector/service helpers and new storage endpoints to cooperate with the modular services.
- Voice & TTS
  - Added a gTTS provider with automatic pyttsx3 fallback, expanded audit logging, and folded it into the provider sequence so fallback order is ElevenLabs → gTTS → offline.
  - Reworked the TTS stop pipeline to raise the interrupt flag, clear the playback queue, and leave the worker thread ready for future jobs, fixing cases where new chunks were still spoken after Stop.
- Decision & diagnostics
  - DecisionLayer now delegates to the shared TTS service, emits richer analyzer/vision logs, and keeps the troubleshooting prints inline with the new modules.
- Resources
  - Added a configurable timeout (default 8s) to `/api/resources/voices` so the UI fails fast when the remote voice provider hangs.
- Frontend
  - Added analyzer settings modal, analyzer/memory config mappers, and expanded settings UI to surface provider selection, fallbacks, and new API fields.
  - Synced chat/settings components with the backend schema so media, analyzer, and memory options stay editable from the UI.


version: 0.3
- Config & Backend
  - Moved the default config into constants/default_config.py, expanded it with system/core sections, voice module settings, STT defaults, and snake_case audio/vision keys.
  - Config service now logs recursive updates, exposes set_config_value, validates user_id, and config routes can read/write system prompts while history fetch supports offsets.
- Voice & Conversation
  - Introduced a shared voice_state controller and wired it through VAD, streaming, and TTS so listening/waiting/speaking stages stay in sync.
  - Added ElevenLabs TTS integration with per-module settings, sanitized streamed speech (# removal, emoji stripping), and skipped synthesis when voice is disabled.
  - VAD listener now deduplicates transcripts, honours the new trigger bypass flag, normalizes config keys, and guards processing with async locks to block self-trigger loops.
- Vision
  - Added an Apple FastVLM provider and structured provider configs, including capture metadata in summaries and optional frame dumps controlled via config.
  - Capture worker now supports monitor/window modes, clamps invalid monitor indices, and reports when the active window falls outside the capture region.
- Frontend & Settings
  - Refactored config mappers into domain utilities aligned with the backend schema and renamed the API client method to updateConfig$.
  - Added Core/System settings views (system prompt editor, theme/language switches, cognitive analyzer controls) and new ConfigService helpers for system endpoints.
  - Theme service now persists the selected theme and initializes stored preferences.
- UI & Components
  - Introduced notification and skeleton shared components plus an emoji picker with a data generation script and bundled emoji dataset.
  - Refreshed chat/settings/layout styles and tabs to surface the new settings groups and debug affordances.


version: 0.2
- Backend
  - Broke out reusable config/constants modules (rules, prompts, paths, indicators, errors, visual, etc.) and updated initialization to preload them.
  - Extracted the vision stack into `backend/modules/vision` with dedicated service/analyzer/worker, refreshed moral & cognitive analyzers and initialization hooks.
  - Introduced `backend/modules/voice` with an async VAD listener, configurable wake words, REST controls (`/api/voice/mode/*`) and safe stubs in `voice_service`.
  - Persisted LLM reasoning in a new `reasoning` table; FastAPI history responses now merge `<think>…</think>` back into message content, and deletions cascade to reasoning rows.
  - Adjusted instructor/API pipeline: vision context is appended via `[CONTEXT:VISUAL]` plus explicit `[INSTRUCTION]` cues so models reliably use screen data.
  - Updated lorebook/RAG services, config service, database helpers, and run loop wiring to match the new module layout.
  - Refreshed backend requirements (added `webrtcvad`, vision OCR/YOLO deps), committed `requirements.lock`, and shipped a CUDA 12.1 torch manifest.

- Frontend
  - Introduced a reusable `message-renderer` module (markdown pipes, text/code/thinking blocks) and rewired chat UI to use it.
  - Restyled chat/history components, lorebook modals, websocket service, and mocks to support thinking blocks and richer formatting.
  - Added project-level `package.json`/`package-lock.json`, bundled `marked` + typings, and updated build tooling/run script to start both frontend and backend.

- Voice & Logging
  - Added detailed VAD logging (trigger hits/misses, self-trigger detection), trigger-word configuration via config, and ensured async scheduling works from PortAudio callbacks.
  - Created REST endpoints to start/stop/status VoiceMode, wired WebSocket stubs, and ensured STT segments flow through the decision layer only when triggers fire.

- UX polish
  - Redesigned the thinking block with LIM palette, accordion-style expand/collapse, and auto-collapse after streaming.
  - Ensured reasoning removal on history deletion and tightened audit logs around VAD, visual context, and API generation flows.


version: 0.1
- Migrated TTS module from z-waif
- Reworked and styled chat interface (action icons, message input, send/reroll/stop buttons)
- Added visual debug log with expandable details
- Implemented basic UI settings with partial + global config sync
- Connected audio module to backend
- Created reusable low-level utilities
- Added LLM initiative engine and preload script
- Introduced preset editor for temperature settings (UI accessible)
- Integrated API router logging & auditing
- Added extensible SQLite database with message history support
- Implemented system device info retrieval (microphone, speakers, etc.)
- Introduced speech-to-text (STT) service
- Migrated utility features from z-waif
- Added memory search behavior
- Improved interaction with voice input

